  "prompt": "How is TRP (target rating point) calculated mathematically? What factors affect it?",
  "response": "TRP (Target Rating Point) is calculated by multiplying two key factors:\n\nMathematical Calculation:\nTRP = Reach % x Average Frequency\n\nFactors affecting TRP:\n1. Audience Reach\n- Percentage of target demographic exposed to media\n- Total unique viewers/listeners\n- Geographic coverage\n\n2. Average Frequency\n- Number of times target audience is exposed to media message\n- Repetition of advertisement/content\n- Media vehicle selection\n\n3. Demographic Targeting\n- Age\n- Gender\n- Income level\n- Occupation\n- Consumer behavior\n\n4. Media Channel\n- Television\n- Radio\n- Digital platforms\n- Print media\n- Outdoor advertising\n\n5. Time of Exposure\n- Specific time slots\n- Peak viewing/listening hours\n- Day parts\n\n6. Ad Placement\n- Program context\n- Channel selection\n- Position within content\n\n7. Media Cost\n- Budget allocation\n- Cost per thousand impressions\n- Efficiency of media buy\n\nThe goal is to maximize TRP by optimizing reach and frequency within the target demographic, ensuring efficient and effective media communication.",
